headline: Symbotic Stock Cut to Sell at UBS. Why Walmart Can’t Be the Only Big Customer.
summary: The firm downgraded  Symbotic  to Sell from Neutral in a research note Tuesday, lifting its price target to $35 from $27.  Walmart is Symbotic’s flagship customer, with the robotics company acquiring Walmart’s advance systems and robotics business earlier this year, and the retailer agreeing to fund the development of new automation systems.

headline: Ballistic Ventures Welcomes Former Roblox, Box, Walmart Security Exec Julie Tsai as CISO-in-Residence
summary: Ballistic Ventures, the venture capital firm dedicated exclusively to funding and incubating entrepreneurs and innovations in cybersecurity, today announced Julie Tsai has joined the firm as its newest CISO-in-Residence. A seasoned cybersecurity leader with more than 20 years of experience driving security and engineering excellence across Silicon Valley, Tsai brings deep expertise in building modern, resilient security programs and guiding organizations through transformative growth.
